# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLE PLAYBOOK — solo founder, idea → validated MVP
# Demonstrates: tier_min=solo, deep complexity, 7 stages, methodology chain
# =============================================================================

slug: solo-idea-to-validated-mvp
title: "Idea → Validated MVP launch"
version: "0.1.0"
status: draft
last_reviewed: 2026-05-17
maintainers: ["faion"]
content_id: 287aa85a2870d3a8

tier_min: solo
complexity: deep
context: [solo]
persona_hints: [P1, P2]                 # Solo SaaS Builder, Indie Hacker (internal)

intent: |
  Raw idea in a notebook → paid landing page + working MVP with first 5 paying users.

scope: |
  Solo founder takes one raw idea from notebook to a launched MVP, exit-criteria
  is a written go/no-go decision backed by problem evidence, scoped spec, shipped
  product, and at least 5 paying customers (or a clean kill).

non_goals:
  - "Team scaling, hiring, or fund-raising — out of scope"
  - "Multi-product portfolio strategy — single-idea playbook"
  - "Enterprise-grade security/compliance — covered in pro/geek playbooks"

prerequisites:
  - "Founder has at least one candidate idea (any form: notebook, voice memo, tweet)"
  - "Access to a credit card for landing page tooling (~$30 total stack)"

success_criteria:
  - "Written JTBD statement for the chosen idea"
  - "10 problem-interview notes captured"
  - "1-page spec with explicit scope cuts"
  - "Paid landing page live with checkout"
  - "5 paying customers OR documented go/no-go kill decision"
  - "Decision doc with evidence trail (interviews, metrics, learnings)"

stages:
  - name: "Discovery"
    intent: "From multiple raw ideas to one chosen problem with documented JTBD."
    tasks:
      - "Generate idea variants and pick top 1-3 by founder-market fit"
      - "Define the Job-To-Be-Done and the painful workflow it replaces"
      - "Survey 10 prospects for problem severity and frequency"
    methodologies:
      - slug: idea-generation
        path: solo/research/market-researcher/idea-generation
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      - slug: jobs-to-be-done
        path: solo/research/researcher/jobs-to-be-done
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      - slug: problem-validation
        path: solo/research/researcher/problem-validation
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
    outputs:
      - "Idea brief (1 page)"
      - "JTBD statement"
      - "10 problem-interview notes"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance if ≥7/10 interviews confirm the pain is top-3 in their workflow.
      Pivot to a different idea variant if 4-6 confirm. Kill if ≤3.

  - name: "Validate"
    intent: "Confirm willingness-to-pay before any code is written."
    tasks:
      - "Define value proposition tied to the JTBD"
      - "Run 5 follow-up interviews focused on pricing signal"
      - "Identify minimum viable pricing tier"
    methodologies:
      - slug: value-proposition-design
        path: solo/research/researcher/value-proposition-design
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      - slug: pricing-research
        path: solo/research/researcher/pricing-research
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      - slug: user-interviews
        path: solo/research/researcher/user-interviews
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
    outputs:
      - "Value-prop canvas"
      - "Pricing hypothesis with 3 tiers"
      - "5 willingness-to-pay quotes"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance if ≥3/5 prospects say "yes, I would pay $X today" with a specific
      number. Pivot pricing/scope if vague. Kill if pricing softens on every call.

  - name: "Spec"
    intent: "Smallest possible build scope with explicit cuts."
    tasks:
      - "Write 1-page spec covering only the validated workflow"
      - "Cut anything not on the critical path to first payment"
      - "Define acceptance criteria per feature"
    methodologies:
      - slug: writing-specifications
        path: solo/sdd/sdd-planning/writing-specifications
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      - slug: spec-structure
        path: solo/sdd/sdd-planning/spec-structure
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      # GAP — see gaps[] below
    outputs:
      - "spec.md (1 page max)"
      - "explicit non-goals list"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance if spec fits on one page AND all features map to acceptance criteria.
      Iterate spec if either fails.

  - name: "Build"
    intent: "Working MVP that delivers the validated value, nothing more."
    tasks:
      - "Implement only spec items in order of dependency"
      - "Skip features that don't block first-payment flow"
      - "Deploy to a real URL daily, however ugly"
    methodologies:
      - slug: writing-implementation-plans
        path: solo/sdd/sdd-planning/writing-implementation-plans
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      - slug: impl-plan-100k-rule
        path: solo/sdd/sdd-planning/impl-plan-100k-rule
        required: false
        tier_gate: solo
    outputs:
      - "Working URL with the validated workflow end-to-end"
      - "Implementation log (what shipped, what was cut)"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance when a stranger can complete the validated workflow without help.
      Stay in Build if anyone needs hand-holding.

  - name: "Beta"
    intent: "5 friendly users run the MVP under real conditions."
    tasks:
      - "Invite 5 prospects from Discovery interviews"
      - "Observe usage; do not pre-explain features"
      - "Log every confusion point"
    methodologies:
      # GAP — see gaps[] below
      - slug: user-interviews
        path: solo/research/researcher/user-interviews
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
    outputs:
      - "5 session-observation notes"
      - "Bug + confusion log"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance if ≥3/5 reach the value moment unaided. Iterate UX if 1-2.
      Re-spec if 0.

  - name: "Launch"
    intent: "Paid landing page live; first paying users converted."
    tasks:
      - "Build paid landing with checkout"
      - "Convert beta users to paying customers"
      - "Open public sign-up"
    methodologies:
      # GAP — see gaps[] below
    outputs:
      - "Live paid landing URL"
      - "First 5 paid invoices"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance if ≥5 paying customers in 14 days post-launch. Else Decide stage.

  - name: "Decide"
    intent: "Written go/no-go backed by evidence."
    tasks:
      - "Compile evidence trail: interviews + metrics + paying-user feedback"
      - "Write explicit decision: continue / pivot / kill"
      - "If continue: define next 30-day milestone"
    methodologies:
      # GAP — see gaps[] below
    outputs:
      - "Decision doc with evidence and next-30-days plan (or kill rationale)"
    decision_gate: |
      Required output: a written decision. No 'maybe'. No 'see how it goes'.

common_pitfalls:
  - "Building before Validate stage — easy to confirmation-bias your way into code"
  - "Cutting Decide stage when the MVP feels 'almost there' — that's exactly when it matters"
  - "Treating Discovery interviews as sales calls — kills signal"

quality_checklist:
  - "Can I show a stranger the decision doc and they understand WHY we shipped/killed?"
  - "Did I actually cut something during Spec, or did I just rename items?"
  - "Did the 5 paying users find me, or did I beg friends?"

related_playbooks:
  - solo-landing-page-conversion
  - solo-pricing-experiment

token_budget_estimate: 18000
cli_invocations:
  human:  "faion get-content solo-idea-to-validated-mvp --format md"
  agent:  "faion get-content solo-idea-to-validated-mvp --format context"
  json:   "faion get-content solo-idea-to-validated-mvp --format json"

changelog:
  - version: "0.1.0"
    date: 2026-05-17
    note: "Initial draft from brainstorm-2026-05-17, P1 unit, global-flow angle"

# BLOCK policy: this playbook cannot move to status: published until gaps == [].
gaps:
  - methodology_slug: mvp-scope-cutting-template
    expected_tier: solo
    blocks_stage: 3
    note: "Spec stage references it but no concrete 'what to cut' rubric exists yet"
  - methodology_slug: founder-market-fit-self-assessment
    expected_tier: solo
    blocks_stage: 1
    note: "Discovery 'pick top 1-3 by founder-market fit' has no scoring tool"
  - methodology_slug: solo-go-no-go-decision-rubric
    expected_tier: solo
    blocks_stage: 7
    note: "Decide stage outputs a decision doc but has no rubric for HOW to decide"
  - methodology_slug: paid-landing-checkout-stack
    expected_tier: solo
    blocks_stage: 6
    note: "Launch stage needs a step-by-step on the cheapest checkout stack"
  - methodology_slug: beta-session-observation-protocol
    expected_tier: solo
    blocks_stage: 5
    note: "Beta stage 'observe without explaining' needs a written protocol"
